  "texts": [
    "We can transform Eq.",
    "(28) for σ *, which depends on the number of point masses N, into a function of the macro-parameters only.",
    "By considering the tail of the probability density function, one finds that 99% of the average flux is contained within a circle of radius 10κ 1/2 * θ E.",
    "The resulting size of the image swarm is then given by transforming this circle to the image plane, resulting in an ellipse with axes given by:",
    "Figure 7 shows various micro-image configurations for the three source positions indicated in Fig. 4."
  ]
